 ananova man admits soham kidnapping hoax calls a man has admitted making hoax calls to police investigating the disappearance of soham schoolgirls jessica chapman and holly wells wrexham magistrates court in north wales heard jobless howard youde made three calls to police in cambridgeshire claiming to have abducted the youngsters he was arrested in wrexham in the early hours of august when officers traced the call to a phone box on the town s brook street the year old of queensway hope near wrexham has pleaded guilty to one count of wasting police time on august this year the court was told youde claimed to have no recollection of making the calls having been drinking all day defence lawyer mark arden says the offence was neither premeditated nor calculated but added that this was no excuse he said what he s done is horrific it s unforgivable the distress he s caused the families is unacceptable youde has been released on unconditional bail until november when he will be sentenced the hearing has been adjourned for pre sentence reports although the defendant has been warned custody is an option story filed monday th october yahoo groups sponsor plan to sell a home http us click yahoo com j snna y leaa mvfiaa gsolb tm to unsubscribe from this group send an email to forteana unsubscribe egroups com your use of yahoo groups is subject to http docs yahoo com info terms 